# Transon Visual Editor — overview

A Blockly visual editor for authoring **Transon** JSON-to-JSON templates. It is an embeddable,
**engine-free** component that generates, imports, and strictly round-trips canonical Transon JSON.
Full contract is in `docs/`: `SPEC.md` (what) · `ARCHITECTURE.md` (how) · `metadata-contract.md`
(metadata shape) · `traceability.md` (coverage) · `ROADMAP.md` (sequencing). Read the relevant
section before non-trivial changes and cite IDs.

## Invariants (do not break)

- **JSON is canonical** (AD-003): the Blockly workspace is a projection, never the sole source of truth.
- **Engine-free** (AD-008): no bundled engine; validation/execution/`include`/`file` cross the host
  `EngineProvider`. The engine is authoritative (NFR-004).
- **Strict semantic round-trip** (AD-004, §15.7): in-surface templates preserve meaning; everything
  else takes an explicit unsupported path. Never silently change meaning.
- **Variants over hidden modes** (AD-015): mutually exclusive params become separate block variants,
  derived from engine `modes`.
- **Metadata-driven** (AD-012): the catalog comes from the engine export; no parallel hand-list.
- **UI ≠ semantics** (§21.12): keep UI-only Blockly metadata out of the executable template.

## Scope guard (§4)

A visual Transon template editor — not a workflow platform, no-code backend, or general visual
programming environment. No backend persistence in v1 (AD-006). If a change needs new behavior,
update `docs/SPEC.md` first (§21.2) and never renumber IDs (§21.1).
